{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9oEoy9wKwjzHJjaGks4p8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the relevant files. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Report: Settlement Transaction Builders & Patterns\n\n### Files Read\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` (538 lines)\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` (224 lines)\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts` (336 lines)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` (216 lines)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/fairness.ts` (40 lines)\n\n---\n\n## **settle-tx.ts — Full Settlement Transaction Builder**\n\n### Exports (Public API)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n}\n\nexport interface SettleResult {\n  txSignature: string;\n  resultHash: Buffer;\n  resultSide?: number;\n  winningEntryIndex?: number;\n  winner: string;\n}\n\nexport async function settleMatch(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\nexport async function settleLordRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\nexport async function settleRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\n\nexport class PermanentSettleError extends Error\nexport class TransientSettleError extends Error\n```\n\n### Key Imports\n```typescript\nimport { createHash } from \"node:crypto\";\nimport { performance } from \"node:perf_hooks\";\nimport { Connection, Keypair, PublicKey, SystemProgram, Transaction, TransactionInstruction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport { decodeCoinflipMatch, decodeCoinflipConfig, decodeLordRound, decodeLordConfig, type DecodedJackpotRound } from \"./account-decoder.js\";\nimport { COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID } from \"../tx-builder.js\";\n```\n\n### Instruction Discriminators (From IDL)\n**Pattern**: Extract discriminators from IDL at module load time, not hardcoded:\n```typescript\nfunction getInstructionDiscriminator(\n  idl: { instructions: Array<{ name: string; discriminator: number[] }> },\n  instructionName: string,\n): Buffer {\n  const instruction = idl.instructions.find((entry) => entry.name === instructionName);\n  if (!instruction) throw new Error(`Instruction ${instructionName} not found in IDL`);\n  return Buffer.from(instruction.discriminator);\n}\n\nconst SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(coinflipIdl, \"settle\");\nconst CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(lordIdl, \"claim_payout\");\n```\n\n### PDA Derivation\n\n**Coinflip Config PDA**:\n```typescript\nfunction deriveConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Lord Config PDA**:\n```typescript\nfunction deriveLordConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"lord_config\")],\n    LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Match PDA** (derived in fairness.ts):\n```typescript\nexport function deriveMatchPda(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), matchId],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Lord Round PDA** (derived in tx-builder.ts):\n```typescript\nexport function deriveLordRoundPda(matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"jackpot_round\"), matchId],\n    LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Instruction Data Encoding\n\n**Settle (Coinflip)**: discriminator(8) + secret(32) = 40 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeSettleData(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n**Claim Payout (Lord)**: discriminator(8) + matchId(8) + secret(32) = 48 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeClaimPayoutData(matchId: Buffer, secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR, matchId, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n### Result Derivation (Fairness)\n**Formula**: `SHA256(secret || entropy || game_pda || algo_ver)`\n```typescript\nfunction deriveResult(\n  secret: Buffer,\n  entropy: Buffer,\n  matchPdaBytes: Buffer,\n  algoVer: number,\n): Buffer {\n  return createHash(\"sha256\")\n    .update(secret)\n    .update(entropy)\n    .update(matchPdaBytes)\n    .update(Buffer.from([algoVer]))\n    .digest();\n}\n```\n\n### **settleMatch() — Coinflip Settlement**\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Retrieve secret from DB\n2. Transition round phase: `locked` → `settling`\n3. Log `settle_submitted` event\n4. Fetch in parallel: match account, config account, entropy account, latest blockhash\n5. Decode accounts using IDL-driven decoders (no manual byte offsets)\n6. Pre-compute result hash and determine winner\n7. Calculate fees: `(pool * 300 / 10000)` bps\n8. Build settle instruction with 8 accounts\n9. Create, sign, and submit transaction\n10. Confirm with `confirmTransaction()`\n11. Update DB: phase → `settled`, store result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_tx\n12. Log `settle_confirmed` event with detailed metrics\n\n**Account Order in Settle Instruction**:\n```typescript\nconst instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n  keys: [\n    { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 0: caller\n    { pubkey: matchPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },               // 1: coinflip_match\n    { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: config\n    { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },          // 3: slot_hashes sysvar\n    { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 4: treasury\n    { pubkey: creator, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                  // 5: creator\n    { pubkey: opponent, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 6: opponent\n    { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 7: system_program\n  ],\n  programId: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  data: encodeSettleData(secret),\n});\n```\n\n**Winner determination** (binary):\n```typescript\nconst resultSide = resultHash[0]! % 2;  // 0 or 1\nconst winner = resultSide === creatorSide ? creator : opponent;\n```\n\n**Timing instrumentation**:\n```typescript\ndbMs, fetchMs, buildMs, sendMs, confirmMs, dbWriteMs, totalMs\n```\n\n### **settleLordRound() — Lord of RNGs Settlement**\n\n**Similar flow to coinflip, with differences**:\n\n1. Decode `JackpotRound` and `LordConfig` accounts\n2. Pre-compute result: derive result hash, then compute winning offset via weighted modulo\n3. **Weighted winner selection** (entry-based):\n   ```typescript\n   const raw = resultHash.readBigUInt64LE(0);\n   const winningOffset = raw % roundData.totalAmountLamports;\n   \n   let cumulative = 0n;\n   let winnerEntryIndex = -1;\n   let winner = roundData.entries[0]?.player;\n   for (const [index, entry] of roundData.entries.entries()) {\n     cumulative += entry.amountLamports;\n     if (winningOffset < cumulative) {\n       winnerEntryIndex = index;\n       winner = entry.player;\n       break;\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Account order in Claim Payout instruction** (7 accounts):\n   ```typescript\n   const instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n     keys: [\n       { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 0: caller (receives rent refund)\n       { pubkey: roundPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },               // 1: jackpot_round\n       { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: lord_config\n       { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },          // 3: slot_hashes sysvar\n       { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 4: treasury\n       { pubkey: winner, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                   // 5: winner\n       { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 6: system_program\n     ],\n     programId: LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n     data: encodeClaimPayoutData(matchIdBuf, secret),\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. DB storage includes `result_side: winnerEntryIndex` (not binary)\n6. Event data includes `winningEntryIndex`, `winningOffset`, `totalAmountLamports`, `rentRefund`\n\n### **settleRound() — Router**\n```typescript\nexport async function settleRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult> {\n  const round = await deps.db.getRoundByPda(pda);\n  if (!round) throw new PermanentSettleError(`Round not found in DB: ${pda}`);\n  \n  if (round.game === \"lord\") return settleLordRound(deps, pda);\n  return settleMatch(deps, pda);\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n```typescript\nexport class PermanentSettleError extends Error {\n  readonly permanent = true;\n}\n\nexport class TransientSettleError extends Error {\n  readonly permanent = false;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **settlement.ts — Settlement Worker (Polling & Detection)**\n\n### Purpose\nPolls the chain for server-owned rounds ready for settlement, detects locked matches, and triggers settlement callbacks.\n\n### Exports\n```typescript\nexport interface SettlementWorkerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKey: PublicKey;\n  pollIntervalMs: number;\n  onSettleReady?: (pda: string) => Promise<void>;\n  isFinalized?: (pda: string) => boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface SettlementWorker {\n  start(): void;\n  stop(): void;\n  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n  poll(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createSettlementWorker(deps: SettlementWorkerDeps): SettlementWorker\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n**Account filtering by phase**:\n```typescript\nconst PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE = 1;        // Coinflip\nconst LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE_VALUE = 1;   // Lord\n```\n\n**Coinflip discovery** (by dataSize):\n```typescript\nconst coinflipAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [{ dataSize: coinflipMatchSize() }],\n});\n```\n\n**Lord discovery** (by discriminator):\n```typescript\nconst lordAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter()],\n});\n```\n\n**Discovered PDA tracking** (prevents re-processing):\n```typescript\nconst discoveredPdas = new Set<string>();\nconst readyPdas = new Set<string>();\nconst undecodeablePdas = new Set<string>();\n```\n\n**Round state machine**:\n- On first detection: `created` → `locked` (update DB with `target_slot`)\n- On target slot reached: call `onSettleReady(pda)` callback\n- On finalization: clean up tracking sets\n\n**Finalization cleanup**:\n```typescript\nif (deps.isFinalized?.(pda)) {\n  discoveredPdas.delete(pda);\n  readyPdas.delete(pda);\n  return;\n}\n```\n\n**Timing logs**:\n```typescript\nslotMs, coinflipFetchMs, lordFetchMs, totalMs, currentSlot, slotTime\n```\n\n---\n\n## **account-decoder.ts — IDL-Driven Account Decoding**\n\n### Exports (All Decode Functions)\n\n**Coder Setup** (instantiated once):\n```typescript\nconst coinflipCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(coinflipIdl as Idl);\nconst closecallCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(closecallIdl as Idl);\nconst lordCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(lordIdl as Idl);\n```\n\n**Coinflip Decoding**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCoinflipMatch(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipMatch\nexport function decodeCoinflipConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipConfig\nexport function coinflipMatchSize(): number\n```\n\n**Lord Decoding**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeLordRound(data: Buffer): DecodedJackpotRound\nexport function decodeLordConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedLordConfig\nexport function lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): { memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string } }\n```\n\n**CloseCall Decoding** (for future use):\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallRound\nexport function decodeCloseCallConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallConfig\nexport function closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): { memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string } }\n```\n\n**Encode functions** (for integration tests):\n```typescript\nexport async function encodeCoinflipMatch(fields: DecodedCoinflipMatch): Promise<Buffer>\nexport async function encodeCoinflipConfig(fields: DecodedCoinflipConfig): Promise<Buffer>\n```\n\n### Type Conversion Helpers\n```typescript\nfunction bnToBigInt(bn: InstanceType<typeof BN>): bigint\nfunction roundPhaseToNumber(phase: Record<string, object>): number  // Waiting=0, Active=1, Locked=2, Resolving=3, Settled=4, Refunded=5\nfunction closeCallPhaseToNumber(phase: Record<string, object>): number  // Open=0, Settled=1, Refunded=2\nfunction outcomeToNumber(outcome: Record<string, object>): number  // Pending=0, Green=1, Red=2, Refund=3\n```\n\n### Decoded Interfaces (All BigInt, camelCase)\n\n**DecodedCoinflipMatch**:\n```typescript\n{\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: bigint;\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: number[];\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  resultHash: number[];\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  createdAt: bigint;\n  matchId: number[];\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**DecodedJackpotRound**:\n```typescript\n{\n  matchId: number[];\n  server: PublicKey;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: number[];\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  entries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  totalAmountLamports: bigint;\n  distinctPlayers: number;\n  createdAt: bigint;\n  countdownStartedAt: bigint;\n  countdownEndsAt: bigint;\n  targetEntropySlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  resultHash: number[];\n  winningOffset: bigint;\n  winningEntryIndex: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **tx-builder.ts — Create Transaction Builders**\n\n### Exports (Create Transactions Only)\n\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\nexport const LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\n\nexport function deriveLordRoundPda(matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number]\n\nexport interface BuildCreateMatchTxParams {\n  connection: Connection;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildCreateMatchTxResult {\n  transaction: string;  // Base64-serialized partially-signed\n  matchPda: PublicKey;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(params: BuildCreateMatchTxParams): Promise<BuildCreateMatchTxResult>\n\nexport interface BuildCreateLordRoundTxParams {\n  connection: Connection;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildCreateLordRoundTxResult {\n  transaction: string;\n  roundPda: PublicKey;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport async function buildCreateLordRoundTx(params: BuildCreateLordRoundTxParams): Promise<BuildCreateLordRoundTxResult>\n```\n\n### Create Match Instruction Data\n**Layout**: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + amount(8, u64 LE) + side(1) + matchId(8) = 57 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeCreateMatchData(\n  commitment: Buffer,\n  amountLamports: number,\n  side: number,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): Buffer {\n  const amount = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  amount.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(amountLamports));\n  return Buffer.concat([CREATE_MATCH_DISCRIMINATOR, commitment, amount, Buffer.from([side]), matchId]);\n}\n```\n\n### Create Match Accounts (5 accounts)\n```typescript\nkeys: [\n  { pubkey: creator, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },                    // 0: creator (payer)\n  { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: false },   // 1: server\n  { pubkey: matchPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                  // 2: match account (created)\n  { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 3: coinflip_config\n  { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 4: system_program\n]\n```\n\n### Create Lord Round Instruction Data\n**Layout**: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + amount(8, u64 LE) + matchId(8) = 48 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeCreateRoundData(\n  commitment: Buffer,\n  amountLamports: number,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): Buffer {\n  const amount = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  amount.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(amountLamports));\n  return Buffer.concat([CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR, commitment, amount, matchId]);\n}\n```\n\n### Create Lord Round Accounts (5 accounts)\n```typescript\nkeys: [\n  { pubkey: creator, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },                    // 0: creator (payer)\n  { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 1: server (pays rent)\n  { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: lord_config\n  { pubkey: roundPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 3: round account (created)\n  { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 4: system_program\n]\n```\n\n### Key Pattern: Partial Signing\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\ntx.feePayer = creator;\ntx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\ntx.lastValidBlockHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\ntx.partialSign(serverKeypair);  // Only server signs — creator signs client-side\n\nconst serialized = tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false }).toString(\"base64\");\nreturn { transaction: serialized, matchPda, lastValidBlockHeight };\n```\n\n---\n\n## **fairness.ts — Utility Helpers**\n\n### Exports\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\n\nexport function generateSecret(): Buffer  // 32 random bytes\nexport function generateMatchId(): Buffer  // 8 random bytes\nexport function computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer  // SHA256(secret)\nexport function deriveMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number]\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Summary: Key Patterns**\n\n| Aspect | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Discriminators** | Extracted from IDL at module load, never hardcoded |\n| **PDA Derivation** | Seeds constructed explicitly; no string interpolation |\n| **Account Decoding** | IDL-driven via BorshAccountsCoder; no manual byte offsets |\n| **Instruction Data** | Buffer.concat with explicit discriminator + field order |\n| **Accounts in Instructions** | Order matches on-chain program exactly; metadata (isSigner, isWritable) must match |\n| **Transaction Building** | Partial signing pattern: server signs, client co-signs later |\n| **Phase Management** | Round state transitions tracked in DB; enum variants converted to numbers |\n| **Result Calculation** | SHA256 of (secret \\|\\| entropy \\|\\| pda \\|\\| algo_ver); binary for coinflip, weighted offset for lord |\n| **Entropy** | First 32 bytes of slot_hashes sysvar account |\n| **Fee Calculation** | `(pool * 300) / 10000` bps (3% total) |\n| **Error Handling** | Permanent vs. Transient errors for retry logic |\n| **Timing Instrumentation** | Multiple checkpoints logged for debugging RPC latency |\n\n---\n\n## **Module Dependencies**\n\n- **settle-tx.ts** imports:\n  - `account-decoder.ts` (decode functions, types)\n  - `tx-builder.js` (PROGRAM_IDs)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs)\n  \n- **settlement.ts** imports:\n  - `account-decoder.ts` (decode, filter, size)\n  - `tx-builder.js` (PROGRAM_IDs)\n  \n- **account-decoder.ts** imports:\n  - `@coral-xyz/anchor` (BorshAccountsCoder)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs)\n  \n- **tx-builder.ts** imports:\n  - `fairness.js` (deriveMatchPda)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs for PROGRAM_IDs)\n  \n- **fairness.ts** imports:\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDL for PROGRAM_ID)\n\n---\n\nThis completes the comprehensive reading of the settlement transaction builder system. All files are read-only; the system is fully implemented and operational."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af2de18b4cf37ab9a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57025\ntool_uses: 7\nduration_ms: 73390</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3173b348-180a-4cf2-ac38-47c17bdb617e","uuid":"430a2f6f-b6c2-4ecb-8895-b698e3919b13","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` in its entirety. Also read any related files that show how coinflip and lordofrngs settlement transaction builders work. Look at imports, function signatures, PDA derivation, remaining accounts patterns, and how they build/send transactions. Also check what's exported from the module. Report the full file contents and patterns.","agentId":"af2de18b4cf37ab9a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have all the relevant files. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete Report: Settlement Transaction Builders & Patterns\n\n### Files Read\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` (538 lines)\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` (224 lines)\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts` (336 lines)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` (216 lines)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/fairness.ts` (40 lines)\n\n---\n\n## **settle-tx.ts — Full Settlement Transaction Builder**\n\n### Exports (Public API)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey;\n}\n\nexport interface SettleResult {\n  txSignature: string;\n  resultHash: Buffer;\n  resultSide?: number;\n  winningEntryIndex?: number;\n  winner: string;\n}\n\nexport async function settleMatch(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\nexport async function settleLordRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\nexport async function settleRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>\n\nexport class PermanentSettleError extends Error\nexport class TransientSettleError extends Error\n```\n\n### Key Imports\n```typescript\nimport { createHash } from \"node:crypto\";\nimport { performance } from \"node:perf_hooks\";\nimport { Connection, Keypair, PublicKey, SystemProgram, Transaction, TransactionInstruction } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL as coinflipIdl, LordofrngsIDL as lordIdl } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport { decodeCoinflipMatch, decodeCoinflipConfig, decodeLordRound, decodeLordConfig, type DecodedJackpotRound } from \"./account-decoder.js\";\nimport { COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID } from \"../tx-builder.js\";\n```\n\n### Instruction Discriminators (From IDL)\n**Pattern**: Extract discriminators from IDL at module load time, not hardcoded:\n```typescript\nfunction getInstructionDiscriminator(\n  idl: { instructions: Array<{ name: string; discriminator: number[] }> },\n  instructionName: string,\n): Buffer {\n  const instruction = idl.instructions.find((entry) => entry.name === instructionName);\n  if (!instruction) throw new Error(`Instruction ${instructionName} not found in IDL`);\n  return Buffer.from(instruction.discriminator);\n}\n\nconst SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(coinflipIdl, \"settle\");\nconst CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR = getInstructionDiscriminator(lordIdl, \"claim_payout\");\n```\n\n### PDA Derivation\n\n**Coinflip Config PDA**:\n```typescript\nfunction deriveConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Lord Config PDA**:\n```typescript\nfunction deriveLordConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"lord_config\")],\n    LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Match PDA** (derived in fairness.ts):\n```typescript\nexport function deriveMatchPda(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), matchId],\n    COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Lord Round PDA** (derived in tx-builder.ts):\n```typescript\nexport function deriveLordRoundPda(matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number] {\n  return PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"jackpot_round\"), matchId],\n    LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Instruction Data Encoding\n\n**Settle (Coinflip)**: discriminator(8) + secret(32) = 40 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeSettleData(secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n**Claim Payout (Lord)**: discriminator(8) + matchId(8) + secret(32) = 48 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeClaimPayoutData(matchId: Buffer, secret: Buffer): Buffer {\n  return Buffer.concat([CLAIM_PAYOUT_DISCRIMINATOR, matchId, secret]);\n}\n```\n\n### Result Derivation (Fairness)\n**Formula**: `SHA256(secret || entropy || game_pda || algo_ver)`\n```typescript\nfunction deriveResult(\n  secret: Buffer,\n  entropy: Buffer,\n  matchPdaBytes: Buffer,\n  algoVer: number,\n): Buffer {\n  return createHash(\"sha256\")\n    .update(secret)\n    .update(entropy)\n    .update(matchPdaBytes)\n    .update(Buffer.from([algoVer]))\n    .digest();\n}\n```\n\n### **settleMatch() — Coinflip Settlement**\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Retrieve secret from DB\n2. Transition round phase: `locked` → `settling`\n3. Log `settle_submitted` event\n4. Fetch in parallel: match account, config account, entropy account, latest blockhash\n5. Decode accounts using IDL-driven decoders (no manual byte offsets)\n6. Pre-compute result hash and determine winner\n7. Calculate fees: `(pool * 300 / 10000)` bps\n8. Build settle instruction with 8 accounts\n9. Create, sign, and submit transaction\n10. Confirm with `confirmTransaction()`\n11. Update DB: phase → `settled`, store result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_tx\n12. Log `settle_confirmed` event with detailed metrics\n\n**Account Order in Settle Instruction**:\n```typescript\nconst instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n  keys: [\n    { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 0: caller\n    { pubkey: matchPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },               // 1: coinflip_match\n    { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: config\n    { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },          // 3: slot_hashes sysvar\n    { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 4: treasury\n    { pubkey: creator, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                  // 5: creator\n    { pubkey: opponent, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 6: opponent\n    { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 7: system_program\n  ],\n  programId: COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID,\n  data: encodeSettleData(secret),\n});\n```\n\n**Winner determination** (binary):\n```typescript\nconst resultSide = resultHash[0]! % 2;  // 0 or 1\nconst winner = resultSide === creatorSide ? creator : opponent;\n```\n\n**Timing instrumentation**:\n```typescript\ndbMs, fetchMs, buildMs, sendMs, confirmMs, dbWriteMs, totalMs\n```\n\n### **settleLordRound() — Lord of RNGs Settlement**\n\n**Similar flow to coinflip, with differences**:\n\n1. Decode `JackpotRound` and `LordConfig` accounts\n2. Pre-compute result: derive result hash, then compute winning offset via weighted modulo\n3. **Weighted winner selection** (entry-based):\n   ```typescript\n   const raw = resultHash.readBigUInt64LE(0);\n   const winningOffset = raw % roundData.totalAmountLamports;\n   \n   let cumulative = 0n;\n   let winnerEntryIndex = -1;\n   let winner = roundData.entries[0]?.player;\n   for (const [index, entry] of roundData.entries.entries()) {\n     cumulative += entry.amountLamports;\n     if (winningOffset < cumulative) {\n       winnerEntryIndex = index;\n       winner = entry.player;\n       break;\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Account order in Claim Payout instruction** (7 accounts):\n   ```typescript\n   const instruction = new TransactionInstruction({\n     keys: [\n       { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 0: caller (receives rent refund)\n       { pubkey: roundPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },               // 1: jackpot_round\n       { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: lord_config\n       { pubkey: entropyAccount, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },          // 3: slot_hashes sysvar\n       { pubkey: treasury, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 4: treasury\n       { pubkey: winner, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                   // 5: winner\n       { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 6: system_program\n     ],\n     programId: LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n     data: encodeClaimPayoutData(matchIdBuf, secret),\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. DB storage includes `result_side: winnerEntryIndex` (not binary)\n6. Event data includes `winningEntryIndex`, `winningOffset`, `totalAmountLamports`, `rentRefund`\n\n### **settleRound() — Router**\n```typescript\nexport async function settleRound(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult> {\n  const round = await deps.db.getRoundByPda(pda);\n  if (!round) throw new PermanentSettleError(`Round not found in DB: ${pda}`);\n  \n  if (round.game === \"lord\") return settleLordRound(deps, pda);\n  return settleMatch(deps, pda);\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n```typescript\nexport class PermanentSettleError extends Error {\n  readonly permanent = true;\n}\n\nexport class TransientSettleError extends Error {\n  readonly permanent = false;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **settlement.ts — Settlement Worker (Polling & Detection)**\n\n### Purpose\nPolls the chain for server-owned rounds ready for settlement, detects locked matches, and triggers settlement callbacks.\n\n### Exports\n```typescript\nexport interface SettlementWorkerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKey: PublicKey;\n  pollIntervalMs: number;\n  onSettleReady?: (pda: string) => Promise<void>;\n  isFinalized?: (pda: string) => boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface SettlementWorker {\n  start(): void;\n  stop(): void;\n  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n  poll(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createSettlementWorker(deps: SettlementWorkerDeps): SettlementWorker\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n**Account filtering by phase**:\n```typescript\nconst PHASE_LOCKED_VALUE = 1;        // Coinflip\nconst LORD_PHASE_ACTIVE_VALUE = 1;   // Lord\n```\n\n**Coinflip discovery** (by dataSize):\n```typescript\nconst coinflipAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [{ dataSize: coinflipMatchSize() }],\n});\n```\n\n**Lord discovery** (by discriminator):\n```typescript\nconst lordAccounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n  filters: [lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter()],\n});\n```\n\n**Discovered PDA tracking** (prevents re-processing):\n```typescript\nconst discoveredPdas = new Set<string>();\nconst readyPdas = new Set<string>();\nconst undecodeablePdas = new Set<string>();\n```\n\n**Round state machine**:\n- On first detection: `created` → `locked` (update DB with `target_slot`)\n- On target slot reached: call `onSettleReady(pda)` callback\n- On finalization: clean up tracking sets\n\n**Finalization cleanup**:\n```typescript\nif (deps.isFinalized?.(pda)) {\n  discoveredPdas.delete(pda);\n  readyPdas.delete(pda);\n  return;\n}\n```\n\n**Timing logs**:\n```typescript\nslotMs, coinflipFetchMs, lordFetchMs, totalMs, currentSlot, slotTime\n```\n\n---\n\n## **account-decoder.ts — IDL-Driven Account Decoding**\n\n### Exports (All Decode Functions)\n\n**Coder Setup** (instantiated once):\n```typescript\nconst coinflipCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(coinflipIdl as Idl);\nconst closecallCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(closecallIdl as Idl);\nconst lordCoder = new BorshAccountsCoder(lordIdl as Idl);\n```\n\n**Coinflip Decoding**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCoinflipMatch(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipMatch\nexport function decodeCoinflipConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipConfig\nexport function coinflipMatchSize(): number\n```\n\n**Lord Decoding**:\n```typescript\nexport function decodeLordRound(data: Buffer): DecodedJackpotRound\nexport function decodeLordConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedLordConfig\nexport function lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): { memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string } }\n```\n\n**CloseCall Decoding** (for future use):\n```typescript\nexport function decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallRound\nexport function decodeCloseCallConfig(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallConfig\nexport function closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter(): { memcmp: { offset: number; bytes: string } }\n```\n\n**Encode functions** (for integration tests):\n```typescript\nexport async function encodeCoinflipMatch(fields: DecodedCoinflipMatch): Promise<Buffer>\nexport async function encodeCoinflipConfig(fields: DecodedCoinflipConfig): Promise<Buffer>\n```\n\n### Type Conversion Helpers\n```typescript\nfunction bnToBigInt(bn: InstanceType<typeof BN>): bigint\nfunction roundPhaseToNumber(phase: Record<string, object>): number  // Waiting=0, Active=1, Locked=2, Resolving=3, Settled=4, Refunded=5\nfunction closeCallPhaseToNumber(phase: Record<string, object>): number  // Open=0, Settled=1, Refunded=2\nfunction outcomeToNumber(outcome: Record<string, object>): number  // Pending=0, Green=1, Red=2, Refund=3\n```\n\n### Decoded Interfaces (All BigInt, camelCase)\n\n**DecodedCoinflipMatch**:\n```typescript\n{\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: bigint;\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: number[];\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  resultHash: number[];\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  createdAt: bigint;\n  matchId: number[];\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**DecodedJackpotRound**:\n```typescript\n{\n  matchId: number[];\n  server: PublicKey;\n  phase: number;\n  commitment: number[];\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  entries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  totalAmountLamports: bigint;\n  distinctPlayers: number;\n  createdAt: bigint;\n  countdownStartedAt: bigint;\n  countdownEndsAt: bigint;\n  targetEntropySlot: bigint;\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;\n  resultHash: number[];\n  winningOffset: bigint;\n  winningEntryIndex: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## **tx-builder.ts — Create Transaction Builders**\n\n### Exports (Create Transactions Only)\n\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\nexport const LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\n\nexport function deriveLordRoundPda(matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number]\n\nexport interface BuildCreateMatchTxParams {\n  connection: Connection;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildCreateMatchTxResult {\n  transaction: string;  // Base64-serialized partially-signed\n  matchPda: PublicKey;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(params: BuildCreateMatchTxParams): Promise<BuildCreateMatchTxResult>\n\nexport interface BuildCreateLordRoundTxParams {\n  connection: Connection;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  matchId: Buffer;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildCreateLordRoundTxResult {\n  transaction: string;\n  roundPda: PublicKey;\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n\nexport async function buildCreateLordRoundTx(params: BuildCreateLordRoundTxParams): Promise<BuildCreateLordRoundTxResult>\n```\n\n### Create Match Instruction Data\n**Layout**: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + amount(8, u64 LE) + side(1) + matchId(8) = 57 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeCreateMatchData(\n  commitment: Buffer,\n  amountLamports: number,\n  side: number,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): Buffer {\n  const amount = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  amount.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(amountLamports));\n  return Buffer.concat([CREATE_MATCH_DISCRIMINATOR, commitment, amount, Buffer.from([side]), matchId]);\n}\n```\n\n### Create Match Accounts (5 accounts)\n```typescript\nkeys: [\n  { pubkey: creator, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },                    // 0: creator (payer)\n  { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: false },   // 1: server\n  { pubkey: matchPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                  // 2: match account (created)\n  { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 3: coinflip_config\n  { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 4: system_program\n]\n```\n\n### Create Lord Round Instruction Data\n**Layout**: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + amount(8, u64 LE) + matchId(8) = 48 bytes\n```typescript\nfunction encodeCreateRoundData(\n  commitment: Buffer,\n  amountLamports: number,\n  matchId: Buffer,\n): Buffer {\n  const amount = Buffer.alloc(8);\n  amount.writeBigUInt64LE(BigInt(amountLamports));\n  return Buffer.concat([CREATE_ROUND_DISCRIMINATOR, commitment, amount, matchId]);\n}\n```\n\n### Create Lord Round Accounts (5 accounts)\n```typescript\nkeys: [\n  { pubkey: creator, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },                    // 0: creator (payer)\n  { pubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },    // 1: server (pays rent)\n  { pubkey: configPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },               // 2: lord_config\n  { pubkey: roundPda, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },                 // 3: round account (created)\n  { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false }, // 4: system_program\n]\n```\n\n### Key Pattern: Partial Signing\n```typescript\nconst { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\ntx.feePayer = creator;\ntx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\ntx.lastValidBlockHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\ntx.partialSign(serverKeypair);  // Only server signs — creator signs client-side\n\nconst serialized = tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false }).toString(\"base64\");\nreturn { transaction: serialized, matchPda, lastValidBlockHeight };\n```\n\n---\n\n## **fairness.ts — Utility Helpers**\n\n### Exports\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID: PublicKey\n\nexport function generateSecret(): Buffer  // 32 random bytes\nexport function generateMatchId(): Buffer  // 8 random bytes\nexport function computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer  // SHA256(secret)\nexport function deriveMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, matchId: Buffer): [PublicKey, number]\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Summary: Key Patterns**\n\n| Aspect | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Discriminators** | Extracted from IDL at module load, never hardcoded |\n| **PDA Derivation** | Seeds constructed explicitly; no string interpolation |\n| **Account Decoding** | IDL-driven via BorshAccountsCoder; no manual byte offsets |\n| **Instruction Data** | Buffer.concat with explicit discriminator + field order |\n| **Accounts in Instructions** | Order matches on-chain program exactly; metadata (isSigner, isWritable) must match |\n| **Transaction Building** | Partial signing pattern: server signs, client co-signs later |\n| **Phase Management** | Round state transitions tracked in DB; enum variants converted to numbers |\n| **Result Calculation** | SHA256 of (secret \\|\\| entropy \\|\\| pda \\|\\| algo_ver); binary for coinflip, weighted offset for lord |\n| **Entropy** | First 32 bytes of slot_hashes sysvar account |\n| **Fee Calculation** | `(pool * 300) / 10000` bps (3% total) |\n| **Error Handling** | Permanent vs. Transient errors for retry logic |\n| **Timing Instrumentation** | Multiple checkpoints logged for debugging RPC latency |\n\n---\n\n## **Module Dependencies**\n\n- **settle-tx.ts** imports:\n  - `account-decoder.ts` (decode functions, types)\n  - `tx-builder.js` (PROGRAM_IDs)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs)\n  \n- **settlement.ts** imports:\n  - `account-decoder.ts` (decode, filter, size)\n  - `tx-builder.js` (PROGRAM_IDs)\n  \n- **account-decoder.ts** imports:\n  - `@coral-xyz/anchor` (BorshAccountsCoder)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs)\n  \n- **tx-builder.ts** imports:\n  - `fairness.js` (deriveMatchPda)\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDLs for PROGRAM_IDs)\n  \n- **fairness.ts** imports:\n  - `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` (IDL for PROGRAM_ID)\n\n---\n\nThis completes the comprehensive reading of the settlement transaction builder system. All files are read-only; the system is fully implemented and operational."}],"totalDurationMs":73390,"totalTokens":57025,"totalToolUseCount":7,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":727,"cache_read_input_tokens":49980,"output_tokens":6314,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":727},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
